## Compliance Checklist (Weekly Review)
```
[ ] API rate limit usage: Peak usage stayed below 80% of Kalshi limits
[ ] Cancel-to-fill ratio: Below 5.0 for all hours
[ ] Order stuffing check: No hour with > 50 orders/hr sustained 2+ hours
[ ] Audit log integrity: Compliance logs are complete and unmodified
[ ] No rejected orders due to rate limiting (would appear in Kalshi error logs)
[ ] Bot version logged in all audit records matches deployed version
[ ] All manual overrides logged with reason and approver
[ ] Record retention: Backups confirmed for audit/trade/config records
```

## Guardrails
- Rate limiter wraps 100% of order and cancellation calls — no exceptions for "just this one"
- Audit logs are append-only and encrypted — never delete or modify historical records
- Any pattern that triggers a scrutiny flag requires human review before trading resumes
- Self-imposed limits are always set conservatively below Kalshi's hard limits
- Keep a written record of every parameter change with rationale and approver — config is compliance evidence
